              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Password inputs should be disguised by default. Midline ellipses are used to represent each character of the password being entered. (••••••••)</p>
              <span class="hca-text--body-2">Show/Hide Password</span>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">If you choose to enable/disable visibility for the password being entered, you may use the visibility-off and visibility-on icon paired with "Show" or "Hide" to indicate the action the user will be taking if they interact with it.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">This button or actionable toggle should be right-aligned above the password field, and in line with the label to its left.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
